  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then chop your <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potatoes </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and most of your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> (save some for garnish!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until cooked through and starting to crisp – these are your<strong> smoky potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684835956608-x200.jpg",
